This version of Terminaux is a revolution of the entire project that contains many exciting features packed with significant improvements to existing features. This version is a bridge to what eventually becomes the seventh major version of Terminaux, 7.0.

### Changes

This release contains a variety of changes, including, but not limited to:

- `[+]` Added audio cues for terminal reader
- `[+]` Added more color features, such as color blending, color contrast, color tints and shades, and more
- `[+]` Added console markup
- `[+]` Added aligned text writers
- `[+]` Added beep synth
- `[+]` Added more reader keybindings
- `[+]` Added cyclic writers and renderables
- `[+]` Added cyclic screen
- `[+]` Added `TermInfo` argument parsing
- `[+]` Added shell functionality from Nitrocid KS
- `[+]` Added command line argument parsing
- `[*]` Used `TermInfo` to generate escape sequences for common operations
- `[*]` Fixed Mono compatibility
- `[*]` Improved appearance in some elements
- `[*]` Description box for selection style
- `[-]` `TextWriterWrappedColor` to be replaced by `TruncatedText`

Review the commit history if you want to get a deep insight about the changes.

### Feedback?

If you have issues with this version, report to us by [making a new issue ticket](https://github.com/Aptivi/Terminaux/issues/new).

